1
00:00:36,700 --> 00:00:42,060
=Twin Fire Dawn=

2
00:00:42,100 --> 00:00:45,060
=Episode 22=

3
00:00:48,580 --> 00:00:52,180
Didn't expect your taste in shoes
to be this good.

4
00:00:53,380 --> 00:00:57,460
But my taste in people is even better.

5
00:01:12,060 --> 00:01:13,020
I'm back.

6
00:01:16,420 --> 00:01:17,460
Yi.

7
00:01:18,940 --> 00:01:20,100
Cheng Yi, you are back.

8
00:01:27,020 --> 00:01:28,100
What took you so long?

9
00:01:28,620 --> 00:01:29,520
How are your injuries?

10
00:01:29,700 --> 00:01:30,940
They healed a long time ago.

11
00:01:31,260 --> 00:01:32,099
Wasn't this

12
00:01:32,100 --> 00:01:34,060
to give you two some alone time?

13
00:01:34,740 --> 00:01:35,740
You're the thoughtful one.

14
00:01:36,460 --> 00:01:37,620
What happened to your voice?

15
00:01:37,980 --> 00:01:39,979
Just a minor throat injury.

16
00:01:39,980 --> 00:01:41,780
It's nothing serious. It'll heal soon.

17
00:01:42,100 --> 00:01:42,740
By the way,

18
00:01:44,260 --> 00:01:45,259
I brought some wine.

19
00:01:45,260 --> 00:01:47,019
Let's have a drink.

20
00:01:47,020 --> 00:01:47,900
Alright.

21
00:01:48,660 --> 00:01:50,300
Why don't you join us too, Yunqiu?

22
00:01:51,260 --> 00:01:53,820
I'll pass. I'll go prepare something
for you two to eat.

23
00:01:57,980 --> 00:01:58,580
Sit.

24
00:02:09,020 --> 00:02:10,340
Do they look nice, Shaoyuan?

25
00:02:12,420 --> 00:02:13,260
They do.

26
00:02:14,260 --> 00:02:15,820
But I'm not talking about the flowers.

27
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:17,880
I'm talking about
the person holding them.

28
00:02:18,340 --> 00:02:19,860
You're teasing me again.

29
00:02:20,740 --> 00:02:21,540
I'm serious.

30
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:24,020
Alright, smooth talker.

31
00:02:24,900 --> 00:02:26,700
Then do you want a taste?

32
00:02:28,420 --> 00:02:29,060
Taste it.

33
00:02:32,140 --> 00:02:36,940
Commander, didn't you say you
needed me for something?

34
00:02:41,460 --> 00:02:42,900
Wasn't I told to come later?

35
00:02:43,980 --> 00:02:45,260
Then I'll leave.

36
00:02:45,540 --> 00:02:46,140
Hey.

37
00:02:46,540 --> 00:02:48,460
If you two have serious business,
hurry up and talk.

38
00:02:54,420 --> 00:02:56,540
(Land Ownership Certificate)

39
00:02:57,220 --> 00:02:58,880
This house and land
were prepared for you.

40
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:00,780
Now all that's left

41
00:03:01,220 --> 00:03:03,540
is for you to marry
a good wife and settle down.

42
00:03:08,820 --> 00:03:11,260
What, lost for words?

43
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:13,220
Thank you, Commander.

44
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:16,260
Why call me Commander all of a sudden?

45
00:03:17,380 --> 00:03:18,460
That's too formal.

46
00:03:20,660 --> 00:03:24,220
Got nervous for a second.
Besides, your status is different now.

47
00:03:24,260 --> 00:03:26,860
Calling you that
also helps build your authority.

48
00:03:31,740 --> 00:03:34,420
My little brother's all grown up now.

49
00:03:34,660 --> 00:03:35,580
Much more sensible too.

50
00:03:37,340 --> 00:03:40,099
Darling, see if there are any good girls,

51
00:03:40,100 --> 00:03:41,340
and introduce one to A'Yi.

52
00:03:42,380 --> 00:03:45,460
Alright. Leave it to me.
I'll make sure to choose carefully for you.

53
00:03:46,820 --> 00:03:48,860
Then I want someone
just as wonderful as you.

54
00:03:50,580 --> 00:03:51,180
That's right.

55
00:03:51,660 --> 00:03:54,539
If you're getting married, it should
be to someone like your sister-in-law.

56
00:03:54,540 --> 00:03:55,580
Enough.

57
00:03:57,860 --> 00:03:58,900
I'm right, aren't I?

58
00:04:05,820 --> 00:04:06,940
Of course.

59
00:04:07,420 --> 00:04:09,499
You are the best.

60
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,540
Alright already, are you two done yet?

61
00:04:12,180 --> 00:04:13,100
You two keep chatting.

62
00:04:13,260 --> 00:04:14,660
I'll go make you something to eat.

63
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:15,780
Thank you.

64
00:04:27,340 --> 00:04:27,980
Come, sit.

65
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:29,060
Alright.

66
00:04:53,820 --> 00:04:54,700
You...

67
00:04:56,820 --> 00:04:57,900
Since when

68
00:04:58,180 --> 00:04:59,900
did you start
putting sugar in your coffee?

69
00:05:05,860 --> 00:05:08,500
Just felt like
trying something different.

70
00:05:41,340 --> 00:05:43,299
I heard she studied abroad too.

71
00:05:43,300 --> 00:05:45,739
A double major
in journalism and the arts.

72
00:05:45,740 --> 00:05:47,980
But she's nothing
more than a pretty face.

73
00:05:48,060 --> 00:05:50,419
If you ask me,
she just loves being in the spotlight.

74
00:05:50,420 --> 00:05:52,340
Always trying to stir up some big story.

75
00:05:52,460 --> 00:05:54,059
Going on and on about justice,

76
00:05:54,060 --> 00:05:55,699
morality, and protecting Yancheng.

77
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:57,659
And dragging
all of us into overtime with her.

78
00:05:57,660 --> 00:05:59,619
Well now she learned her lesson.

79
00:05:59,620 --> 00:06:01,619
How can someone
like her even be a reporter?

80
00:06:01,620 --> 00:06:03,740
She might as well
just go home and get married.

81
00:06:06,540 --> 00:06:07,739
Alright, break it up.

82
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:09,020
Let's go.

83
00:06:25,580 --> 00:06:26,340
(Darling,)

84
00:06:26,700 --> 00:06:27,820
(I miss you very much.)

85
00:06:28,260 --> 00:06:30,140
(But if I want
to make something of myself soon)

86
00:06:30,220 --> 00:06:31,220
(and marry you properly,)

87
00:06:31,320 --> 00:06:33,080
(I have to leave
and make my way in the world.)

88
00:06:33,700 --> 00:06:35,540
(But lately I've been short on money.)

89
00:06:35,900 --> 00:06:37,260
(I still need your help for now.)

90
00:06:37,500 --> 00:06:39,940
(In the future, I promise
to devote myself to you)

91
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:41,500
(and treat you even better.)

92
00:06:42,860 --> 00:06:44,419
Gu Nianchi, just you wait.

93
00:06:44,420 --> 00:06:45,620
I'll send the money right away.

94
00:06:57,060 --> 00:06:57,780
Commander,

95
00:06:58,180 --> 00:07:00,379
Xue Wan has already
transferred the money.

96
00:07:00,380 --> 00:07:01,440
Ten thousand silver dollars.

97
00:07:01,780 --> 00:07:02,660
Your side?

98
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:05,620
Not the slightest suspicion.

99
00:07:06,820 --> 00:07:08,500
He's still treating me very well.

100
00:07:11,540 --> 00:07:12,620
Shaoyuan,

101
00:07:13,820 --> 00:07:16,260
you're really generous
with someone else's money.

102
00:07:17,060 --> 00:07:18,580
Using my money

103
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:20,380
to support that brat.

104
00:07:22,380 --> 00:07:24,180
I'm your big brother,

105
00:07:25,860 --> 00:07:28,780
yet you've never treated me this well.

106
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,220
Please calm down, Commander.

107
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:37,820
Lu Shaoyuan is cunning.

108
00:07:38,060 --> 00:07:39,220
We need to plan this carefully.

109
00:07:39,680 --> 00:07:41,420
We absolutely
can't let him discover anything.

110
00:07:42,300 --> 00:07:45,060
The Commander's Residence
is heavily guarded by soldiers.

111
00:07:46,980 --> 00:07:48,940
I have to get the military seal back

112
00:07:49,580 --> 00:07:51,020
and reclaim control of the troops.

113
00:07:57,620 --> 00:07:58,940
Spread your fingers a little more.

114
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:02,880
Raise the web between
your thumb and index finger.

115
00:08:03,660 --> 00:08:05,340
I already learned this before.

116
00:08:05,380 --> 00:08:07,660
Back then, I specially learned it
just to get close to you.

117
00:08:07,900 --> 00:08:09,140
You learned before?

118
00:08:09,180 --> 00:08:09,499
Mm.

119
00:08:09,500 --> 00:08:10,620
You're that good?

120
00:08:11,220 --> 00:08:12,380
Couldn't tell at all.

121
00:08:14,460 --> 00:08:15,260
Come.

122
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:16,300
One.

123
00:08:16,620 --> 00:08:17,420
Two.

124
00:08:17,500 --> 00:08:18,340
Three.

125
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:20,860
That's not my fault.

126
00:08:21,220 --> 00:08:22,500
How is it not your fault?

127
00:08:22,540 --> 00:08:23,820
It's because you distracted me.

128
00:08:24,020 --> 00:08:25,219
When did I distract you?

129
00:08:25,220 --> 00:08:27,220
You're obviously
just too good at this yourself.

130
00:08:28,940 --> 00:08:31,340
I remember when we first met.

131
00:08:32,020 --> 00:08:33,739
- You were lying there.
- Don't say it.

132
00:08:33,740 --> 00:08:34,759
And your leg was like this...

133
00:08:34,759 --> 00:08:35,620
No,

134
00:08:36,460 --> 00:08:37,540
that never happened.

135
00:08:38,420 --> 00:08:39,340
You forgot already?

136
00:08:43,980 --> 00:08:45,420
Then let me help refresh your memory.

137
00:08:45,940 --> 00:08:47,580
That day wasn't like this at all.

138
00:08:48,300 --> 00:08:50,100
- Then what was it like that day?
- That day...

139
00:10:06,260 --> 00:10:10,950
♪How can broken love ever go on?♪

140
00:10:12,260 --> 00:10:17,580
♪How much hope must fade into despair?♪

141
00:10:18,080 --> 00:10:21,660
♪In the blink of an eye,
everything falls apart♪

142
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:25,010
♪Bound by the fate we cannot escape♪

143
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:30,300
♪You and I caught in
this tangled love and hate♪

144
00:10:31,420 --> 00:10:36,610
♪Fragile hearts can hardly bear goodbye♪

145
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:43,270
♪How many times
must pain cut deep before we wake?♪

146
00:10:43,810 --> 00:10:47,190
♪I once gave myself
to you so completely♪

147
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:50,389
♪Still holding on to that heart♪

148
00:10:50,390 --> 00:10:55,529
♪Only to suffer your fatal blow♪

149
00:10:55,530 --> 00:10:59,849
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

150
00:10:59,850 --> 00:11:02,429
♪Yet I approach you with such caution♪

151
00:11:02,430 --> 00:11:04,709
♪How could a stand in ever have♪

152
00:11:04,710 --> 00:11:08,259
♪The right to be loved by you?♪

153
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:12,789
♪If love is nothing
more than endless schemes♪

154
00:11:12,790 --> 00:11:15,320
♪Used and abandoned in the end♪

155
00:11:15,460 --> 00:11:17,409
♪Still I walk into♪

156
00:11:17,410 --> 00:11:21,009
♪The trap you set without regret♪

157
00:11:21,010 --> 00:11:25,059
♪How desperately
I long to hold you close♪

158
00:11:25,060 --> 00:11:27,639
♪Yet keep it buried deep inside♪

159
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:29,799
♪A stand in can never cross♪

160
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:33,239
♪The shortest distance between us♪

161
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:38,210
♪If love can
make someone lose themselves♪

162
00:11:38,370 --> 00:11:43,040
♪Then let me stay by your side♪

163
00:11:45,820 --> 00:11:47,389
♪A substitute♪

164
00:11:47,390 --> 00:11:52,390
♪Needs no reason♪

